column5: It was around 4 30 AM when I reeled in the world record walleye last night.  Surprisingly caught while bottom bouncing for steelies at my local haunt. She was a gigantic 26 pounds! Boy was I excited!                                          Until I woke up!  crap
Great dream Kemper. Thanks for the report.  I usually just fall off a cliff.

HAHAHAHAHA I had one of them Monday. It was +12 outside and we woke up to a fresh 4 inches of snow. It was more of a wish then a dream.LOL     UMMMMM What were doing on C,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Never mind. LOL
Lucky duck, mine are usually of plane crashes and trying to run as fast as i can but dont go anywhere lol
Does Big Cliff know about your dreams, Roy ??
Great Lew, Ruined my lap top  hahaha
well she was beautiful...  i mean  aw crap
Well you're still doing better than me....not only am I not even fishing, I can't seem to dream about it these days  The trick for you is to turn that dream into a reality  Maureen
TOO funny guys....as coffee is comming out my nose.....
In my case I often dream about catching record steel from the Kispiox or the Skeena.  When I wake up I realize I'm reviving a monster eel instead.
Hmm... almost 1 am now, I am going to try your hot spot soon....
Jezzus Lew...I just spewed coffee all over my keyboard and monitor
too funny guys.  Thanks for posting Kemper.
